    "Moreover, our evidence indicates that the Catholic school civic advantage acknowledged by some scholars (Coleman & Hoffer, 1987, pp. 212-213; Macedo, 2000, pp. 234-235; Prud'homme, 2022) appears to be a more general religious school civic advantage.",
    "The data do not support the theoretical concerns of harmful civic effects from private schooling (Dewey, 1916, p. 85; Gutmann, 1987; Shober, 2012, pp. 192-194; Stitzlein, 2023 Stitzlein, [2017]], p. 14).",
    "Based on the empirical evidence, private schooling does not threaten democracy.",
    "Educational pluralism seems to be a boon, and not a bane, for civic outcomes (Berner, 2017, pp. 73-103; McCluskey, 2020, pp. 18-19).",
    "Our findings yield a key insight for public policy as well as an important qualification."
